<section id="h21003">
<title>
<emphasis id="Sinusoids" effect="bold">

Sinusoids

</emphasis>


</title>




<para id="p1032">
<link id="a1050" target-id="Figure_1">

Figure 1

</link>

 shows a curve whose shape is commonly referred to as a sinusoid. 
Eliminating the syntax required by the Java programming language, the expression 
used to produce the data plotted in 

<link id="a1051" target-id="Figure_1">

Figure 1

</link>

 was:

</para>





<code id="pre1002" display="block">f(x) = cos(2*pi*x/50) + sin(2*pi*x/50)</code>




<para id="p1033">
As you can see, this function is composed of two components, one cosine 
component and one sine component.

</para>





